<plot>Francis Coppola explains how he adapted the original novel by Mario Puzo. Coppola shows (for the first time) his original "prompt book" containing all of his notes and observations that would be used to plan the screenplay and production design of the now classic film. An intimate look inside the mind of the young as yet unknown director, circa 1971.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?202211</url></doc>
